        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 24 at 5:48PM EDT until June 24 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Marion Springs to near Chesaning to near
Flushing, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

These severe storms will be near...
Flushing, Chesaning, Montrose, and Marion Springs around 555 PM
EDT.
Flint and Beecher around 600 PM EDT.
St. Charles and Mount Morris around 605 PM EDT.
Clio around 610 PM EDT.
Birch Run around 615 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include Brant,
Fenmore, Burt, Fosters, Layton Corners, and Rankin.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
